P(HH|H) = \frac{P(H|HH) * P(HH)}{P(H)}
P(H|HH) = 1
P(HH) = \frac{1}{100}
P(H) = \frac{100}{200} = \frac{1}{2}
P(HH|H) = \frac{1}{50}
P(HH) = \dfrac{\text{# of ways to pick H and get the HH coin}}{\text{# of ways to pick H}} = \dfrac{2}{100}
= \frac{1}{2}\frac{98}{100}
= 1*\frac{1}{100}
\frac{1*\frac{1}{100}}{\frac{1}{100}+\frac{1}{2}\frac{98}{100}}
 = \frac{1}{50}
